The most popular book written by George Orwell is undoubtedly "1984". It is a dystopian novel published in 1949 that depicts a totalitarian society in which the government has total control over every aspect of people's lives, including their thoughts and emotions. The novel has become a classic of modern literature and is known for its portrayal of the dangers of government surveillance, propaganda, and censorship. It has been translated into more than 65 languages and has sold millions of copies worldwide.